

PURO

   from the Spanish
   puro
   pure, unmixed

   purong-puro
   very pure

   Puro asukal ito.
   This is all sugar.

   Puro reklamo ka.
   All you do is complain.

   Puro kawayan ang ginamit nila.
   What they used was all bamboo.

   The native Tagalog word for “pure” or “unadulterated” is lantáy.
